The paper deals with the study of structural restrictions on automata and their induced language families, which falls under the scope of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also compares the language families induced by deterministic finite automata and biautomata, which involves the study of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses orderability, which is a topic in mathematical logic and set theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the landscape of classical language families, which involves the study of complexity theory and algorithms (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also discusses the characterization of language families, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
